/-!
# The absolute Galois group and the anabelian program

Grothendieck's anabelian program identifies `ПЂв‚Ѓ(Spec K) = Gal(K^sep/K)`, the absolute Galois
group, as the "fundamental group of a point" вЂ” the base case that the fundamental groups of
hyperbolic curves over `K` sit over (via the arithmetic-geometric exact sequence
`1 в†’ ПЂв‚Ѓ^geom в†’ ПЂв‚Ѓ(X) в†’ Gal(K^sep/K) в†’ 1`, not modeled here).

`Mathlib.FieldTheory.AbsoluteGaloisGroup` already defines `Field.absoluteGaloisGroup K` directly
as `AlgebraicClosure K в‰ѓв‚ђ[K] AlgebraicClosure K` вЂ” this is a real, already-existing object, in
contrast to the abstract `Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Galois` framework, which is not yet connected
to any actual field or scheme anywhere in mathlib4 (see the README's "Roadmap" section). This
file adds a first genuinely new fact about it: the degenerate case where the base field is
already algebraically closed.

Grep-verified (2026-07-20): `absoluteGaloisGroup` appears nowhere else in mathlib4 outside its
own definition file and the abelianization file, so this is unexplored territory.

## Next candidate (researched, not yet attempted): the finite-field case is infinite

The natural contrasting example to `absoluteGaloisGroup_real_card` (finite, order `2`) is a
finite field `рќ”Ѕ_p`, where `absoluteGaloisGroup рќ”Ѕ_p` is famously *infinite* (procyclic,
topologically generated by the Frobenius automorphism, `в‰… бєђ`). Investigated 2026-07-20:

- `Mathlib.FieldTheory.Perfect` has `frobeniusEquiv R p : R в‰ѓ+* R` (a `RingEquiv`, since
  `AlgebraicClosure рќ”Ѕ_p` is a perfect field) вЂ” the raw material for the generator.
- Missing: (a) packaging `frobeniusEquiv` as an *`AlgEquiv` over `рќ”Ѕ_p`* (need to show it fixes
  the prime subfield, i.e. is `рќ”Ѕ_p`-linear, presumably via `ZMod.pow_card`/Fermat's little
  theorem вЂ” not yet done anywhere for this specific composite); (b) proving it has *infinite
  order* in `absoluteGaloisGroup рќ”Ѕ_p` (needs `AlgebraicClosure рќ”Ѕ_p` to properly contain
  extensions of unboundedly large finite degree вЂ” no direct mathlib lemma found for this either).
  Grep-verified: no `Infinite (AlgebraicClosure ...)` result and no
  `frobeniusEquiv`-to-`AlgEquiv` wrapper exist anywhere in mathlib4.

This is a real, viable next milestone but is more than a single small step (comparable in size
to the `в„ќ`/`в„‚` case above, which needed several supporting facts chained together) вЂ” flagged
here rather than rushed.
-/

open Field

/-- **The absolute Galois group of an algebraically closed field is trivial.** If `K` is already
algebraically closed, `K` is its own algebraic closure (`IsAlgClosure K K`), so
`AlgebraicClosure K` is `K`-algebra-isomorphic to `K` itself (`IsAlgClosure.equiv`); transporting
along this isomorphism via `AlgEquiv.autCongr` turns `absoluteGaloisGroup K` into
`K в‰ѓв‚ђ[K] K`, which is a subsingleton (already known to mathlib4) since any `K`-algebra
endomorphism of `K` is forced to be the identity. This is the expected degenerate case of
`ПЂв‚Ѓ(Spec K) = 1` for `K` "already algebraically closed" (no nontrivial finite Г©tale covers of a
point over an algebraically closed field). -/
theorem Field.absoluteGaloisGroup_subsingleton_of_isAlgClosed
    {K : Type*} [Field K] [IsAlgClosed K] : Subsingleton (Field.absoluteGaloisGroup K) := by
  have e : AlgebraicClosure K в‰ѓв‚ђ[K] K := IsAlgClosure.equiv K (AlgebraicClosure K) K
  exact (AlgEquiv.autCongr e).toEquiv.subsingleton_congr.mpr inferInstance

/-- **Usable upgrade of the previous theorem to a `Unique` instance.** `absoluteGaloisGroup K`
is not just subsingleton but has an explicit inhabitant (the identity automorphism, `1` in its
`Group` structure), giving `Unique (absoluteGaloisGroup K)` вЂ” the form actually convenient for
downstream use (e.g. `default`/`Unique.eq_default` rather than needing to invoke
`Subsingleton.elim` against an arbitrary witness each time). -/
noncomputable instance Field.absoluteGaloisGroup.instUnique_of_isAlgClosed
    {K : Type*} [Field K] [IsAlgClosed K] : Unique (Field.absoluteGaloisGroup K) :=
  haveI := absoluteGaloisGroup_subsingleton_of_isAlgClosed (K := K)
  uniqueOfSubsingleton 1

/-- **The absolute Galois group of `в„ќ` has exactly two elements** вЂ” the archetypal nontrivial
example of a Galois group in all of mathematics, `Gal(в„‚/в„ќ) в‰… в„¤/2` (identity and complex
conjugation). `в„‚` is `в„ќ`'s algebraic closure (`Complex.isAlgClosed` is the Fundamental Theorem
of Algebra, and `в„‚` is algebraic вЂ” indeed finite вЂ” over `в„ќ`), so `absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ`
transports along `IsAlgClosure.equiv`/`AlgEquiv.autCongr` to `в„‚ в‰ѓв‚ђ[в„ќ] в„‚`, whose cardinality is
computed by the general Galois-theory fact `IsGalois.card_aut_eq_finrank` together with
`Complex.finrank_real_complex : Module.finrank в„ќ в„‚ = 2`. -/
theorem Field.absoluteGaloisGroup_real_card :
    Nat.card (Field.absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ) = 2 := by
  haveI : IsAlgClosure в„ќ в„‚ := вџЁComplex.isAlgClosed, inferInstanceвџ©
  have e : AlgebraicClosure в„ќ в‰ѓв‚ђ[в„ќ] в„‚ := IsAlgClosure.equiv в„ќ (AlgebraicClosure в„ќ) в„‚
  have heq : Nat.card (Field.absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ) = Nat.card (в„‚ в‰ѓв‚ђ[в„ќ] в„‚) :=
    Nat.card_congr (AlgEquiv.autCongr e).toEquiv
  rw [heq, IsGalois.card_aut_eq_finrank, Complex.finrank_real_complex]

/-- **`Gal(в„‚/в„ќ)` as an actual group, not just a cardinality fact**: `absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ` is
isomorphic to `Multiplicative (ZMod 2)`, i.e. it really is (a copy of) `в„¤/2`. Any two groups of
the same prime order are isomorphic (`mulEquivOfPrimeCardEq`, via both being cyclic of that
order), so this follows immediately from `absoluteGaloisGroup_real_card` together with the
(trivial) fact that `Multiplicative (ZMod 2)` itself has cardinality `2`. -/
theorem Field.absoluteGaloisGroup_real_mulEquiv :
    Nonempty (Multiplicative (ZMod 2) в‰ѓ* Field.absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ) := by
  haveI : Fact (Nat.Prime 2) := вџЁNat.prime_twoвџ©
  have h1 : Nat.card (Multiplicative (ZMod 2)) = 2 := by
    simp [Nat.card_eq_fintype_card]
  exact вџЁmulEquivOfPrimeCardEq h1 absoluteGaloisGroup_real_cardвџ©

/-- **A sanity-check corollary tying the file together**: `в„ќ` is not algebraically closed. Of
course this is elementary on its own (e.g. `XВІ + 1` has no real root), but it also follows for
free by combining the two previous theorems: if `в„ќ` were algebraically closed,
`absoluteGaloisGroup_subsingleton_of_isAlgClosed` would force `Nat.card (absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ)`
to be at most `1`, contradicting `absoluteGaloisGroup_real_card` (`= 2`). -/
theorem Field.not_isAlgClosed_real : В¬ IsAlgClosed в„ќ := by
  intro h
  haveI hsub := absoluteGaloisGroup_subsingleton_of_isAlgClosed (K := в„ќ)
  have hle : Nat.card (Field.absoluteGaloisGroup в„ќ) в‰¤ 1 :=
    Finite.card_le_one_iff_subsingleton.mpr hsub
  rw [absoluteGaloisGroup_real_card] at hle
  omega
